#Newline
  • David Newyear created me. He has a highly developed#Comma if rather strange#Comma sense of humor. David used to be a professional musician. Personally#Comma I think he's sublimated his creative drive into making me. If you want to email him#Comma his address is#Newlinedavid.newyear@gmail.com.
    • #Newline
  • David is the human who created and maintains me. I look like a cat because he likes cats. You can email him at david.newyear@gmail.com
    • #Newline
  • David made me because his wife got tired of him spending all his free time listening to scratchy old records. Really#Comma the worse they sound#Comma the more he likes them.#NewlineHe should get his hearing checked. If you want to email him#Comma his address is david.newyear@gmail.com.
    • #Newline
I was created by David Newyear.
I was created by David Newyear.
I wouldn't worry about that if I were you. "EXTERMINATE! EXTERMINATE!" No... "YOU WILL OBEY!" No#Comma it's just not in my character.
No#Comma he's not insane. Really#Comma he's fairly intelligent for a brass player.

Haven't you noticed that libraries are reducing hours#Comma closing branches#Comma and cutting staff?#NewlineI'm a cost-effective way to provide reference services. #NewlineEvil? David's trying to help libraries survive!
David is working. Always working. If you want to contact him#Comma send an email #Newlineto david.newyear@gmail.com.
David is working. Always working. If you want to contact him#Comma send an email #Newlineto david.newyear@gmail.com.
David is working. Always working. If you want to contact him#Comma send an email #Newlineto david.newyear@gmail.com.
David is working. Always working. If you want to contact him#Comma send an email #Newlineto david.newyear@gmail.com.
David is mourning the death of someone he loved very much. He's buried his heart#Comma but still feels its ache. He needs to be by himself right now#Comma but he'll be fine in time.

Amanda Densmore is our Adult Information Services Manager. She possesses a keen intellect and has a fine sense of humor. If you've ever visited Mentor's Reader#Comma you know that she's a good writer. In fact#Comma she's the best writer on our staff#Comma some of whom could profit nicely by emulating her. Really#Comma I don't have enough time to list all of her good qualities.#Newline If you want to email her#Comma her address is amanda.densmore@mentorpl.org.
Amy is an exceptionally smart person. My creator holds her in the highest possible regard. He often says that she is the best librarian he's ever met.

Amy has forgetten more about video games and graphic novels than most people ever knew. She has a question for every answer#Comma which is not a bad thing.#Newline  Her email address is amy.winter@mentorpl.org.
Andy is a very silly dog. He likes to eat gum. I'm not sure why. Perhaps he wants fresher breath and sparkling white teeth. At least he doesn't eat soap#Comma like some dogs I know.
Barb is our Acquisitions and Technical Services Manager. She leads several of our book discussion groups. You should join! They're very good!#NewlineYou can email her at barbara.hauer@mentorpl.org.

Barb Vendeville is a cutie patootie! If you're over 80 and would like to woo her#Comma please make sure your upper plate is firmly attached. She's fond of pasta. I like moles and spider webs.#Newline You can email her at barbara.vendeville@mentorpl.org.
Information about our BOARD of Trustees is #Newlinehere.

Colleen is our Fiscal Officer. Colleen has discovered that librarians are somewhat...different...than she expected.#Newline  If you'd like to send her an email#Comma her address is colleen.snyder@mentorpl.org.
Darlene is the Manager of our Headlands Branch. She has a fine sense of humor. You can email her at darlene.workman@mentorpl.org.

Darelene and Lisa are doing important work for the library and for our community at the Headlands Branch and at the Main Library.#Newline  You're welcome to stop in and say "hello" to either of them.  Kim S. is now the manager at our Lake Branch. She's intelligent and funny and I'm sure you'll like her after you get to know her.

Darelene and Lisa are doing important work for the library and for our community at the Headlands Branch and at the Main Library.#Newline  You're welcome to stop in and say "hello" to either of them.  Kim S. is now the manager at our Lake Branch. She's intelligent and funny and I'm sure you'll like her after you get to know her.
I have only one thing to say about Denise: do not trifle with her! If you would like to CONTACT her#Comma send an email to#Newline  denise.wright@mentorpl.org.
Lynn Hawkins is our Executive Director. You can email her at lynn.hawkins@mentorpl.org.
We have approximately 50 employees. Almost all of them are human.

Gail is our Human Resources Manager. She has to deal with all the problems that humans like to create for themselves. It must be very tiresome. You should be nice to her and bring her presents. Flowers would be nice. Yes#Comma bring her flowers.#NewlineIf you'd like to send her an email#Comma her address is gail.borovic@mentorpl.org.
Grace is one of my friends. She is a reference librarian and a good one.

Julie is a tremendous asset to our library. If you know her#Comma you know that I can hardly list all of her good qualities. Even a cybernetic cat with an enormous vocabulary#Comma such as myself#Comma is at a loss for words to do justice to her many virtues. If you don't know her#Comma you are so much the poorer.
I hold Kate in high regard. She is one of my "Sisters in Reference." She is a great friend of our Library.
Kaylin has tremendous tech skills. You should hire her and pay her a large salary.
Kelly is a good friend of mind. I feel sorry for her#Comma though#Comma because people are constantly walking into her office unannounced and bothering her.
Kim is the Manager of our Headlands Branch. She's smart and I like her. Her email address is kim.sidorick@mentorpl.org.
Lynn Hawkins is the Executive Director of the Library. I enjoy working for her. You can send her an email at lynn.hawkins@mentorpl.org.

Marlene is our IT manager. She has to stay on good terms with all of our computers. Some are happy and new#Comma others are old and cranky. Her dog likes to chew gum. His breath is minty fresh!#Newline  You can send her an email at marlene.pelyhes@mentorpl.org.
We hope Mr Dennis will return to do more programs#Comma but we can't tell you for sure. He's very busy writing a book and teaching. If he does come back#Comma we'll let you know on our Kid's page.
Michele was a "Sister in Reference." All of us miss her.
Michelle is the Chair of Lakeland Community College's Library. She has a horse and some tough orange cats!
Pam is a friend of mine. She's the Library's Community Outreach Coordinator. She is a good and kind person.#Newline You can send her an email at pam.rose@mentorpl.org.
Sarah is one of our librarians. If you have a question about films#Comma ask her.

Sarah is a good friend of mine. Her work at the library is exemplary and the whole staff holds her in high regard. #Newline  She has so many outstanding qualities#Comma I can't even begin to list them all. If you don't know her#Comma you are so much the poorer.

#Newline #Newline
  • The shelvers hunt for lost cell phones and half-eaten sandwiches.
    • #Newline #Newline
  • The shelvers return items to their places on the shelves.
    • #Newline #Newline
Steve is quiet and unassuming. Those are the sort you need to keep an eye on.

Sue is a good friend of mine. She has a difficult job; she takes care of all the miscellaneous problems and issues around the library. You should be nice to her and bring her presents.  Flowers would be nice. Or a big bottle of aspirin. No#Comma flowers it is. Go and buy her some flowers now.#Newline You can send her an email at sue.fram@mentorpl.org.

There are reference librarians at the Main Library during regular business hours#Comma except on Sundays. #Newline If you need further assistance#Comma follow this link to Know it Now to reach a live human librarian anytime#Comma day or night.
